            <h1 style="color:#ff0000"><u>Goverment Scholarships</u></h1>
            <h3><b>(1) MYSY</b></h3>
            <li><b>Eligibility:</b> Student must have secured 80 or more Percentile in 12th Science and family income must be less than Rs. 6 lakh/annum.</li>
            <li><b>Amount of Scholarship</b>: Rs. 50,000/- or 50% of tuition fees whichever is less.</li>

            <h3><b>(2) Freeship Card for Scheduled Caste Candidates for Post Metric Scholarship</b></h3>
            <li><b>Eligibility:</b> Student must belong to SC or ST category and family income must be less than Rs. 2,50,000/annum.</li>
            <li><b>Amount of Scholarship</b>: 100% tuition fees.</li>

            <h3><b>(3)   Scholarship for SEBC/OBC Category</b></h3>
            <li><b>Eligibility:</b>Student must belong to OBC category and family income must be less than Rs. 2,50,000/annum. </li>
            <li><b>Amount of Scholarship:</b>Rs. 50,000/-</li>

            <h3><b>(4)Tuition Fee Waiver Scheme (TFWS)</b></h3>
            <li>Under the TFW scheme, students do not have to pay the tuition fee (Rs. 60,000 to Rs. 1,00,000 approx) in SFI.</li>
            <li>5% of total seats shall be filled by TFW scheme, e.g. 60 seats than 3 seats shall be filled by TFWS.</li>
            <li>Students whose parent's income is less than Rs. 8 lakh/annum are eligible for TFWS.</li>
            <li>Admission is strictly on merit numbers through the admission committee.</li>
            <li>TFW scheme shall be applicable for the complete duration of the course(4 Years).</li>
